President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Richard Ashooh of New Hampshire as Assistant Secretary of Commerce, Export Administration. Ashooh is currently the Director of Economic Partnerships at the University System of New Hampshire and has extensive experience in the aerospace industry. Trump also intends to nominate Callista L. Gingrich of Virginia as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Holy See. Gingrich is the President and CEO of Gingrich Productions and has authored several books. In addition, President Trump intends to designate Dr. Poonam Alaigh as Acting Under Secretary of Veterans Affairs for Health. Dr. Alaigh has served as the Senior Advisor to the Under Secretary for Health and has experience in healthcare policy and management.